main event: On March 9, 1965, an unidentified object was observed descending below the horizon near Larson Air Force Base in Washington.
interesting points: The object was well-defined with clear lights and emitted no sound., The sighting lasted approximately 9 seconds., A letter mentions investigations of a landing area in Canada related to a similar sighting., The observer initially thought a local boy took a look at the object., There were reports of similar sightings around the same time, including complaints from the public about unusual objects in the sky.
witness description: The witness had previously studied UFOs and indicated the object was real.
